ce:section.ce:para:
From the results (Fig. 2
                         and Table 3
                        ), it was evident that the as-synthesized AgNPs showed moderate to good antibacterial activity. Bio-AgNPs showed better activity against B. subtilis (Fig. 2o), CoNS (Fig. 2p), and S. aureus (Fig. 2u), whereas Che-AgNPs showed better activity against E. coli (Fig. 2q), K. pneumoniae (Fig. 2r), and P. aeruginosa (Fig. 2t). Similar activity was observed against P. vulgaris (Fig. 2s). It was observed that Bio-AgNPs were effective against gram + bacteria, whereas Che-AgNPs were effective against gram- bacteria (Fig. 2o − 2u).
